Kelly Natoli (born 12 June, 1987 in Columbia, Maryland) is a Narrative Film/Production|Film/Video Media Studies senior at Pomona College.

I am grew up in a town of about 500 people in Western Maryland (that's the one that's shaped like a gun) called New Market. It was founded in 1745 and is pretty much just a historical landmark with lots of antique stores.

I'm a Media Studies liaison this year.

I am also one of those people who are not ashamed to admit that they like television better than film. Yes, I am a heathen; a heathen with a short attention span.

I also like watching (not playing, I am very not-good at them) sports. Hockey (San Jose Sharks) is my special favorite. I can "play", and I can "skate". I am pretty much obsessed with Hockey. In the worst way that you can be obsessed with something. :D

I would love to be a screenwriter for television when I "grow up," but I am willing to accept that talent cannot be taught, and so I will most likely be living in San Jose and going to hockey games, begging for employment by the Sharks Organization. It's a solid plan.

In my spare time, I am working to create an elixir that will give me an infinite amount of good ideas and witty things to say.


I also copied and pasted this from a biography I did last semester.


ALSO, I TOTALLY JUST REALIZED HOW ADDICTED I AM TO THIS WIKI!
